1. How to install packages in python

You have to install pip first & use pip3.

https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/installing-packages/

2. How to install package pyautogui?

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/35074294/pip3-install-pyautogui-fails-with-error-code-1-mac-os?utm_medium=organic&utm_source=google_rich_qa&utm_campaign=google_rich_qa

https://github.com/n1nj4sec/pupy/issues/540

Step0. Install Xcode from the Mac App Store. This is a requirement for installing PyObjC. https://pythonhosted.org/pyobjc/install.html
Step1. sudo pip3 install pyobjc-core
Step2. sudo pip3 install pyobjc
Step3. sudo pip3 install Pillow
Step4. sudo pip3 install pyautogui

3. How to clear PyCharm run window?

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27241268/clear-pycharm-run-window?utm_medium=organic&utm_source=google_rich_qa&utm_campaign=google_rich_qa

If you set the keyboard shortcut for 'clear all' to Command + L use this in your python script:

import pyautogui
pyautogui.hotkey('command', 'l')


